<TEXT>
Police used tear gas to subdue 
rioting fans at a professional wrestling tournament and two 
officers were injured in scuffles a police spokesman said Sunday 
Lt Bala Naidoo said one officer was hit in the face and chest 
by a bottlewielding spectator and another was hit on the head 
with a chair during the Saturday night disturbance 
He said an unspecified number of angry berserk fans were 
arrested most of them for using obscene language The cause of the 
violence was not immediately known 
The crowd had gathered for a tournament that featured an 
appearance by a West German wrestler known as Mighty Rambo 
</TEXT>
